  "title": "Internal Auditor",
  "description": "<p>Key Responsibilities:</p><ul><li>Assist in conducting internal audits based on established checklists to ensure accuracy and compliance.</li><li>Perform and conduct internal audits pertaining to various aspects of revenue collections and operating expenses, compliance checks on operational procedures and all forms of safety measures and risk assessments/management.</li><li>Identify, document, and take corrective actions for any non-conforming processes.</li><li>Assist in preparing and presenting audit reports, documenting findings, and highlighting effective processes.</li><li>Collaborate with management to improve audit methods and operational procedures.</li></ul><p>Job Requirements:</p><ul><li>Bachelor's degree in Accounting, Finance or Business.</li><li>Strong attention to detail and analytical thinking skills.</li><li>Good communication skills, both written and verbal.</li><li>Proficiency in Microsoft Excel.</li><li>Inquisitive and pro-active in nature.</li><li>Previous exposure to auditing is a plus</li></ul>",
